article.headline: Hofstra 63, Delaware 61
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) -- Aurimas Kieza scored 16 points in his first start of the season to lead Hofstra to a 63-61 victory over Delaware on Wednesday night. Loren Stokes added 14 points and six assists for the Pride (9-12, 5-6 Colonial), who trailed 26-234 at halftime. Kenny Adeleke had 10 points, seven rebounds and seven steals. Rulon Washington, 6-for-10 on 3-pointers, topped the Blue Hens (12-8, 6-5) with 20 points. Robin Wentt added 17 points and 14 rebounds. Mike Ames, who had 11 points, had a trio of 3-pointers to set a Delaware career record with 212. Kestutis Marchulionis set the previous mark of 211 from 1996-00. Delaware has at least one 3-pointer in its last 401 games. Delaware got to 60-59 on a 3-pointer by Washington with 20 seconds remaining. The Pride then scored their final three points from the foul line, two by Kieza, to make it 63-59 with 11 seconds to player. Calvin Smith hit a layup at the buzzer to finish the scoring.
